              <span id="reviewTextContainer927588581" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer956259727796604358">Lady Nijo is an interesting woman, you can see that in the first few pages. Sadly I feel the book got dry towards the end of the book. Still I&apos;m glad that I picked this book up and I would suggest it to anyone that likes literature about Japan.</span>
  <span id="freeText956259727796604358" style="display:none">Lady Nijo is an interesting woman, you can see that in the first few pages. Sadly I feel the book got dry towards the end of the book. Still I'm glad that I picked this book up and I would suggest it to anyone that likes literature about Japan.</span>
